WEBVTT

00:00.354 --> 00:02.237
Let's pray together.

00:02.257 --> 00:05.662
Yes, Lord, for the joy of all peoples.

00:08.106 --> 00:18.963
And so my prayer is that you would create in us all of us minds and hearts that are world Christian.

00:21.226 --> 00:28.818
And I pray for a select group in this room in whom you have been working already

00:30.050 --> 00:45.747
to incline them toward the serious consideration of going to the least-reached places and peoples of the world, and that through this message, a decisive word would be spoken.

00:49.150 --> 00:50.672
And I ask this in Jesus' name.

00:51.693 --> 00:53.615
Amen.

00:53.635 --> 00:54.837
So you go to the website.

00:55.017 --> 00:59.922
If you go to the website of Bethlehem College in Seminary and you click at the top on Seminary,

01:00.610 --> 01:01.371
Here's what you read.

01:01.411 --> 01:15.872
Shepherds, meaning pastor, scholars, teachers, equipping men to treasure our sovereign God in sacred book for the joy of all peoples through Jesus Christ.

01:16.392 --> 01:17.955
So a seminary for the peoples.

01:20.298 --> 01:23.082
A seminary with sight on the nations.

01:25.045 --> 01:28.850
If you click at the top on college, what you read is this.

01:29.058 --> 01:51.954
We study the great books in the light of the greatest book for the sake of the great commission, a liberal arts college in the reformed classical tradition for the sake of the great commission, a classical education and baked into it a commitment to the global purposes of God.

01:53.376 --> 01:57.202
So seminary for the peoples, a college for the world.

01:58.882 --> 02:03.990
And I cannot tell you how happy I am with those mottos.

02:04.631 --> 02:05.372
I didn't write them.

02:06.253 --> 02:06.814
I love them.

02:08.116 --> 02:13.884
And may the Lord do that for the sake of the nations.

02:14.926 --> 02:28.466
So I have the happy assignment in this message to speak on our all nations charge, Colin, what it means to be a world Christian.

02:29.026 --> 02:29.987
So here's my approach.

02:32.310 --> 02:37.335
First, give a resounding biblical statement of the all nations charge.

02:39.277 --> 02:44.123
Second, give a brief biblical definition of what it means to be a world Christian.

02:46.505 --> 02:50.890
And third, the lion's share of the message.

02:51.671 --> 02:58.258
Deal with three peculiar obstacles that stand in the way of your full

02:58.690 --> 03:06.561
red-blooded, risk-taking, totally in engagement with God's global purpose.

03:07.903 --> 03:09.185
Obstacles that are in your way.

03:12.009 --> 03:21.082
And we're going to do that from Philippians 2 verses 17 and 18, but that's coming in about 15 minutes.

03:21.102 --> 03:26.770
So first, the biblical statement of the All Nations charge.

03:30.274 --> 03:34.819
Jesus said, all authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.

03:35.860 --> 03:47.914
Go therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe everything I've taught you.

03:48.394 --> 03:55.442
And behold, I'm going to be with you always to the end.

03:59.490 --> 04:21.223
that global authority to presume to tell us, to tell every other religion to become Christian, that global authority, that total authority of Jesus over the nations was obtained in a peculiar way, namely by blood.

04:24.988 --> 04:28.754
Revelation 5, 9, worthy are you to take the scroll

04:29.730 --> 04:46.430
and to open its seals, for you were slain, you were slaughtered, and by your blood you ransomed people from every tribe and tongue and people and nation, and you have made them a kingdom, priests to our God, and they shall reign on the earth.

04:48.152 --> 04:54.799
He bought them, and the you is go get them.

04:56.602 --> 04:57.042
Amazing.

04:57.410 --> 05:00.915
There isn't a greater enterprise anywhere in the world.

05:04.179 --> 05:05.882
I lay down my life for the sheep.

05:07.244 --> 05:10.548
I have other sheep that are not of this fold.

05:11.469 --> 05:17.578
I must bring them also and they will listen to my voice and there will be one flock and one shepherd.

05:17.778 --> 05:19.300
How are they going to hear the voice of Jesus?

05:21.623 --> 05:22.264
He's in heaven.

05:22.324 --> 05:26.450
Romans 10.

05:27.618 --> 05:30.141
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

05:30.982 --> 05:34.406
How will they call on Him whom they have not believed?

05:34.706 --> 05:38.250
And how shall they believe in Him whom they have never heard?

05:38.290 --> 05:46.139
And how are they to hear without someone besides Jesus preaching?

05:46.199 --> 05:51.065
And how are they to preach unless they are sent as it is written?

05:51.966 --> 05:52.727
How beautiful.

05:54.549 --> 05:55.410
How beautiful.

05:56.706 --> 06:00.051
are the feet of those who preach the goodness.

06:03.136 --> 06:15.355
Some of you in this room, some are younger, some are middle-aged, and maybe one or two are older, since God's stirring in that direction.

06:16.196 --> 06:16.496
You do.

06:17.718 --> 06:18.520
You know who you are.

06:19.401 --> 06:21.424
You don't know what it means yet fully.

06:21.664 --> 06:25.330
You just sense maybe

06:26.274 --> 06:27.897
That's what I'm supposed to do.

06:30.981 --> 06:34.467
And you ask, how in the world, I do it.

06:34.928 --> 06:37.632
I'm just so ordinary.

06:39.815 --> 06:41.358
And Jesus answers your questions.

06:41.378 --> 06:42.259
Just loud and clear.

06:42.580 --> 06:46.446
You will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes upon you.

06:46.686 --> 06:51.373
And you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem and all Judea and Samaria and to the ends of the earth.

06:51.414 --> 06:52.535
That's how you're going to do it.

06:53.297 --> 06:54.258
There won't be you.

06:59.458 --> 07:05.064
That's my answer to the question, what is the all nations charge?

07:05.725 --> 07:06.085
That's it.

07:07.046 --> 07:09.569
Second, what's a world Christian?

07:11.851 --> 07:14.674
What do we mean by world Christian?

07:17.618 --> 07:29.170
We mean, first, whether you're a goer or a sender, your heart and your mind are engaged with God's mission

07:29.730 --> 07:33.936
to gather redeemed people from all the nations of the world.

07:34.637 --> 07:38.322
Your heart is in world missions.

07:40.625 --> 07:42.027
That's the first thing.

07:42.047 --> 07:58.610
It also means that together with all true Christians everywhere in the world, you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a holy nation.

08:01.186 --> 08:17.990
A people for God's own possession, 1 Peter 2.9, which means, as a world Christian, you are more significantly united to believers in Russia than unbelievers in America.

08:21.656 --> 08:28.946
You are more significantly united to believers in Gaza, Palestinian believers,

08:30.178 --> 08:33.062
than Americans who are unbelievers.

08:33.783 --> 08:38.671
That's what it means to be a world Christian.

08:38.691 --> 08:39.412
Are you a Christian?

08:40.093 --> 08:42.496
That's the question.

08:42.516 --> 08:58.540
If you are, you're so united, far more, to believers in all the peoples than you are to unbelievers in this culture and this nation.

08:58.560 --> 08:59.922
The Global Church

09:00.642 --> 09:15.766
is a holy nation, which means that we are sojourners and exiles in every nation on the planet.

09:17.529 --> 09:19.211
Our citizenship is in heaven.

09:20.674 --> 09:22.917
Our Constitution is the Bible.

09:23.799 --> 09:25.842
Our King is Jesus.

09:26.114 --> 09:31.903
Our homeland is the heavenly Jerusalem and our mission has no borders.

09:33.024 --> 09:35.869
That's what it means to be a world Christian.

09:35.889 --> 09:36.810
What makes you tick?

09:39.014 --> 09:49.389
The people of God, the plan of God, the work of God, the mission of God or some other allegiance.

09:49.409 --> 09:51.933
That's the answer to question number two.

09:51.953 --> 09:53.035
What is a world Christian?

09:54.156 --> 09:55.218
And now we turn

09:56.002 --> 10:04.191
to the obstacles between you and your engagement with that cause.

10:05.833 --> 10:25.074
This is a multi-generational conference, intentionally, meaning we hope there's high school students here, we hope there's middle-aged people here, we hope there's a few, we happy few who are in their 70s and 80s.

10:27.170 --> 10:39.349
It's a multi-generational conference, and I want to address a peculiar obstacle for each group, all right?

10:39.369 --> 10:44.798
I'll name it, and then we'll go to the Bible to see how to overcome it.

10:47.262 --> 10:48.023
The younger group.

10:51.308 --> 10:54.834
In the last 15 years maybe,

10:56.674 --> 11:07.669
There has appeared a form of political correct cowardice.

11:10.973 --> 11:23.410
It takes the form of opposing those whose views you don't like, you oppose the views you don't like by claiming that you don't feel safe when they talk to you.

11:27.202 --> 11:32.587
And you put that into words sometimes with their speeches, violence.

11:32.888 --> 11:35.691
Their speech is violence to me.

11:37.512 --> 11:42.137
And I'm calling that a politically correct form of cowardice.

11:46.702 --> 11:54.770
For example, on a Christian or a secular campus,

11:55.586 --> 12:09.443
Some speaker speaks about the entanglements of Planned Parenthood and abortion and ethnicity and poverty and a group of students, protests, that makes me feel very unsafe.

12:10.785 --> 12:12.267
So don't let him speak here anymore.

12:17.233 --> 12:21.298
I'm calling this politically correct cowardice

12:23.266 --> 12:26.149
in relationship to global missions for a reason.

12:29.312 --> 12:44.827
If that mindset takes deeper and wider root in the Christian community, it will be a huge hindrance to the mission.

12:45.108 --> 12:45.668
Why is that?

12:48.551 --> 12:51.474
Because if you're so committed,

12:53.250 --> 12:59.901
to feeling safe, how will you ever risk your life for Christ?

13:04.468 --> 13:07.694
There is no Christian mission without the surrender of safety.

13:08.475 --> 13:08.735
None.

13:13.944 --> 13:20.114
Matthew 10, 16, behold, I am sending you out as sheep in the midst of wolves.

13:24.002 --> 13:36.337
If you're so fragile and cowardly that you must shut down words that offend you, how will you speak the gospel to those who revile you?

13:36.357 --> 13:48.972
I have a word for you from the Bible to liberate you, and that's coming in about 10 minutes.

13:51.916 --> 13:53.618
Second group, the middle-aged group,

13:54.370 --> 14:03.479
What is a characteristic obstacle for the 30, 40, 50 somethings among us?

14:08.183 --> 14:12.407
I call it unquenchable consumption.

14:15.710 --> 14:24.178
And the consumption I have in mind is not the consumption of the bread of life, the word of God, but the consumption of social media,

14:24.610 --> 14:43.397
movies, the demands of a career, the quest for more and more stuff, another house, another cruise, an Ivy League school for my kids, more and more stuff.

14:43.417 --> 14:52.530
The quest to consume more entertainment, more toys, more travel, more money is insatiable.

14:54.018 --> 14:55.280
It doesn't satisfy.

14:55.300 --> 14:59.405
A life devoted to consumption consumes your life.

15:02.309 --> 15:22.898
Jesus said this, they hear the Word of God, but the cares of this world and the deceitfulness of riches and the desire for other things choke the Word and it proves unfruitful.

15:23.266 --> 15:24.147
No missions.

15:25.768 --> 15:29.232
Missions is killed about the desire for things.

15:32.535 --> 15:33.056
Stuff.

15:38.441 --> 15:46.589
It's a snare that plunges people into ruin and destruction, all the while giving the sensation of success.

15:48.191 --> 15:51.474
A life devoted to unquenchable consumption

15:52.290 --> 16:00.141
more media, more movies, more leisure, more mammon cannot compute with this calculus.

16:03.305 --> 16:04.226
Here's the calculus.

16:04.747 --> 16:19.026
That mindset cannot compute with everyone who has left houses or brothers or sisters or father or mother or children or lands for my sake will receive a hundred fold and will inherit eternal life.

16:20.354 --> 16:23.359
where that kind of calculus doesn't compute?

16:24.260 --> 16:24.561
Like what?

16:26.584 --> 16:27.285
I want stuff.

16:28.447 --> 16:31.011
No, you leave, stuff.

16:32.233 --> 16:37.201
Where that calculus doesn't compute, missions is over.

16:42.530 --> 16:47.698
If you're being lured to that kind of unquenchable consumption, I have a word for you.

16:48.610 --> 16:50.312
which will come in about five minutes.

16:52.354 --> 16:55.778
A word from the Bible that will be liberating for you.

16:58.241 --> 17:07.010
What about us happy few 70-somethings, 80-somethings?

17:07.030 --> 17:12.717
I'm tempted to have you raise your hand, but you may not feel as proud of this as I do.

17:15.920 --> 17:17.522
But proud is the wrong word.

17:20.482 --> 17:23.505
What is our besetting obstacle?

17:24.066 --> 17:27.129
We should be engaged one way or the other.

17:27.389 --> 17:28.270
We should be all in.

17:28.330 --> 17:36.379
It is creeping comfort.

17:38.902 --> 17:41.725
The creep of comfort.

17:44.368 --> 17:50.194
From every corner of our culture, we are told that the biblical command

17:51.042 --> 17:56.869
Let us not grow weary in well-doing has an expiration date.

17:58.191 --> 17:59.653
Like 65 would be.

17:59.673 --> 18:02.075
67 maybe.

18:02.096 --> 18:09.284
It expires.

18:10.706 --> 18:14.531
We no longer exist for accomplishment or creating.

18:14.971 --> 18:17.234
We exist for comfort, for play.

18:18.882 --> 18:31.206
Spend your last decades cramming into your bucket list, as though heaven, which is just over the horizon, as though heaven didn't contain every conceivable joy.

18:33.811 --> 18:39.762
Like, does that make any sense at all to cram into the last

18:40.194 --> 18:47.404
decades of your life, a bucket list of pleasures because you think heaven's going to be boring anyway.

18:47.424 --> 18:49.947
And so I need to get as much now as I can.

18:50.227 --> 18:53.231
That's insane and totally what the world has to say.

18:53.291 --> 18:59.980
That's not what this season of life is for.

19:00.581 --> 19:01.162
This is not.

19:02.784 --> 19:07.410
Near the end of his life, Paul referred to himself only one time as an old man.

19:08.194 --> 19:10.757
I don't know how old he was, he just called himself old once.

19:11.959 --> 19:15.584
You know where he was when he said that, wasn't paradise, it was prison.

19:18.308 --> 19:30.044
Phil, Philemon 1 9, I Paul, an old man, and now a prisoner also for Christ Jesus.

19:30.805 --> 19:31.706
You gotta love him.

19:31.746 --> 19:34.730
You gotta love him.

19:34.770 --> 19:37.714
You gotta put his picture on the wall.

19:39.170 --> 19:40.391
Get a Rembrandt.

19:42.954 --> 19:46.257
That's what I have cost $10.

19:55.786 --> 19:56.747
And here's what he said.

19:59.270 --> 20:01.892
Within Stone's Throw, this martyrdom.

20:02.873 --> 20:04.094
I have fought the good fight.

20:04.695 --> 20:05.876
I have finished the race.

20:06.657 --> 20:08.018
I have kept the faith.

20:09.282 --> 20:13.289
Now I think that means to the end, fought to the end.

20:14.872 --> 20:25.551
Henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness which the Lord the righteous judge will award to me and not only to me but to all those who have loved his appearing.

20:25.912 --> 20:31.943
That's the bucket list.

20:31.963 --> 20:33.746
So if you are feeling

20:35.010 --> 20:37.233
the creep of comfort, like I am.

20:37.433 --> 20:39.215
I feel very threatened by this.

20:41.498 --> 20:47.846
I am more comfortable, more at ease, less pressure in my life right now than ever, ever before.

20:50.509 --> 20:52.491
Pastor is pressure.

20:54.173 --> 20:59.680
My job, 40, 50 hours a week with DG, piece of cake, no pressure.

21:00.922 --> 21:01.703
Every night is free.

21:03.325 --> 21:04.466
Good night, that's dangerous.

21:07.074 --> 21:08.696
I'm preaching to myself here.

21:13.601 --> 21:17.486
Turn with me to Philippians chapter 2, please.

21:18.627 --> 21:21.070
And let's look at Philippians 2, 17 and 18.

21:23.292 --> 21:24.934
This is God's Word to the young.

21:24.954 --> 21:26.295
It's God's Word to the middle age.

21:26.656 --> 21:28.117
It's God's Word to the old.

21:30.160 --> 21:33.163
It's an antidote to cowardice, consumption, and comfort.

21:35.225 --> 21:35.826
And it is

21:36.642 --> 21:46.752
mind-bogglingly counterintuitive, counter-cultural, offensive to many people.

21:52.137 --> 22:05.330
Philippians 2.17, even if I am to be poured out as a drink offering upon the sacrificial offering of your face, I am

22:06.082 --> 22:06.723
glad.

22:10.847 --> 22:14.631
And I rejoice with you all.

22:16.433 --> 22:32.851
Likewise, you should also be glad and rejoice with me as I pour out my life for your faith.

22:32.872 --> 22:35.154
Now, there are three facets.

22:35.874 --> 22:40.319
to the diamond of Christian joy in those two verses, three facets.

22:42.901 --> 22:56.155
And each of them correspond respectively to cowardice issues, consumption issues, and comfort issues.

22:56.175 --> 22:59.799
Let's take them one at a time.

22:59.819 --> 23:03.122
First facet of Christian joy in these verses.

23:04.898 --> 23:11.465
Paul's joy in being poured out on the offering of their faith.

23:12.146 --> 23:23.058
So verse 17, even if I am to be poured out as a drink offering upon the sacrificial offering of your faith, I am glad.

23:23.298 --> 23:26.081
That's joy at being poured out.

23:26.782 --> 23:28.484
Now what does being poured out refer to?

23:28.524 --> 23:30.386
Death.

23:30.818 --> 23:38.429
And there's no doubt that it refers to that because he says in 2 Timothy 4, 6, I am already being poured out.

23:39.892 --> 23:42.576
The time of my departure has come.

23:48.104 --> 23:57.458
So the first facet of Christian joy is Paul's joy at the prospect of dying in the service of the Philippian faith.

24:07.426 --> 24:16.580
He's glad that His life could be taken in the service of their faith.

24:16.601 --> 24:17.502
That's what it says.

24:17.542 --> 24:22.830
That's not natural.

24:24.533 --> 24:25.535
That's supernatural.

24:27.518 --> 24:29.761
The Christian life is supernatural or nothing.

24:33.527 --> 24:35.250
It is one thing to rejoice

24:35.746 --> 24:38.610
because you're the instrument of bringing someone to faith.

24:39.231 --> 24:40.193
That's a great joy.

24:41.835 --> 24:47.444
It's beyond all normal human experience through joys that you get to die to do it.

24:51.069 --> 24:52.551
You get to die to do it.

24:54.895 --> 24:56.097
Nobody does that.

24:56.698 --> 25:05.010
Nobody talks like that except weird people, Christian people, real Christians.

25:11.426 --> 25:12.267
What's behind that?

25:14.170 --> 25:15.132
How can Paul talk like that?

25:16.414 --> 25:17.435
Two things are behind it.

25:18.537 --> 25:20.200
And you know at least one of them.

25:22.082 --> 25:27.230
Philippians 1, 21, he said, for to me to live his Christ and to die is gain.

25:27.811 --> 25:28.893
So that's part of the answer.

25:28.973 --> 25:29.754
What's behind that?

25:30.375 --> 25:36.905
You're going to rejoice that you get to die for the service of their faith.

25:37.707 --> 25:39.890
And he said, already told you it's gain.

25:41.730 --> 25:42.852
That's not the whole answer.

25:45.115 --> 25:48.060
Because that would be true whether he died for somebody's faith or not.

25:48.581 --> 25:50.003
All he has to do is die.

25:52.107 --> 25:59.799
This is about dying in the service of an underage people group that you'd like to see come to faith.

26:02.964 --> 26:07.130
And so the second answer, what's behind this, is Jesus' word to Paul.

26:07.271 --> 26:09.394
He is more blessed to give than to receive.

26:12.962 --> 26:13.583
X2035.

26:14.124 --> 26:22.677
It is blessed or joyful to see another person's joy increase.

26:23.257 --> 26:24.740
That's a happy thing.

26:25.040 --> 26:27.644
If your joy increased, I would rejoice.

26:28.305 --> 26:40.443
It's an even more blessed thing if your joy increases because of my joy expanding through my life into your joy.

26:41.605 --> 26:42.386
That's more.

26:43.650 --> 27:10.949
if I could spend my life so that my vertical delight in knowing Christ and the totality of all the God is for me and Jesus, if I could spend my life so that that joy through my instrumentality became your joy, that would be another reason to say, I am glad to give my life for this.

27:10.969 --> 27:11.890
We call that love.

27:16.898 --> 27:18.019
You know this is true.

27:18.500 --> 27:19.641
You've all experienced it.

27:20.462 --> 27:20.862
You have.

27:21.924 --> 27:36.320
You all know that when your joy is think of an occasion, when your joy or your happiness is given away, it is never cut in half.

27:37.401 --> 27:40.104
It is always doubled.

27:40.124 --> 27:40.645
You know this.

27:42.847 --> 27:45.170
You could think of something day before yesterday.

27:45.986 --> 27:47.508
You did something.

27:47.528 --> 27:49.690
You went beyond your comfort zone.

27:50.531 --> 27:52.353
You did something helpful.

27:53.635 --> 27:58.120
And at the end, you would have been happy staying in your comfort zone.

27:58.180 --> 28:02.966
And now you're doubly happy because you included them.

28:03.006 --> 28:07.911
They got drawn in to the happiness that doubles.

28:08.532 --> 28:10.014
It doesn't cut anything in half.

28:10.294 --> 28:13.778
Giving your life away doesn't cut your happiness in half.

28:15.522 --> 28:17.284
Not of its joy in Jesus.

28:20.829 --> 28:22.070
That's the first facet.

28:22.371 --> 28:28.398
I'll come back around later at the end to apply to the young people.

28:30.481 --> 28:34.966
Second facet of joy is found at the end of verse 17.

28:38.130 --> 28:44.178
I am glad and I rejoice with you all.

28:46.434 --> 28:54.486
So evidently, when he says, I rejoice with you all, they're already rejoicing.

28:56.229 --> 28:56.650
Let me know that.

28:56.710 --> 28:57.451
They're Christians.

28:58.232 --> 28:59.374
He planted this church.

29:02.759 --> 29:04.361
So what are they rejoicing in?

29:04.421 --> 29:05.844
They're already rejoicing.

29:06.004 --> 29:09.249
And now he's enjoying their joy in whatever it is.

29:11.192 --> 29:12.754
What is it?

29:13.026 --> 29:18.273
The second facet of the joy in these verses is he's he's enjoying what they enjoy.

29:18.293 --> 29:21.537
I rejoice with you all.

29:21.817 --> 29:26.303
You're rejoicing and I'm rejoicing with you in what?

29:29.146 --> 29:41.842
He said in chapter 1 verse 25 that he's in prison and he expects I think to have a season of freedom in which he can go visit the Philippians.

29:43.010 --> 29:57.924
And he puts it like this, verse 25, convinced of this, I know that I will remain and continue with you all for your progress and literally joy of faith.

29:58.365 --> 30:01.448
That's what he's referred to as their joy, the joy of faith.

30:04.170 --> 30:08.054
For Paul, joy and faith are inseparable.

30:10.376 --> 30:12.018
When you have saving faith,

30:12.994 --> 30:18.479
You have tasted the sole satisfying value of Jesus.

30:18.600 --> 30:20.501
That's what it means to be converted.

30:21.643 --> 30:25.146
Tasting that the Lord is good.

30:25.166 --> 30:26.127
Those taste buds are dead.

30:27.529 --> 30:29.010
You're made alive and you taste.

30:29.811 --> 30:30.511
The Lord is good.

30:32.233 --> 30:33.134
I like what it tastes.

30:33.154 --> 30:33.555
It's good.

30:36.057 --> 30:37.218
So it means to be saved.

30:39.621 --> 30:41.042
That's the second facet.

30:41.954 --> 30:45.258
of the diamond of Christian joy, the joy of faith.

30:47.180 --> 30:48.342
What does faith rejoice in?

30:48.382 --> 30:50.544
The Word of God.

30:50.805 --> 30:51.706
I get texts for all these.

30:51.806 --> 30:52.687
I'm going to skip the texts.

30:52.707 --> 30:53.348
You can find them.

30:54.109 --> 31:03.420
The Word of God, the love of God, the final salvation of God, suffering, hope of glory of God, God Himself.

31:03.540 --> 31:08.066
I will go to the altar of God, to God my exceeding joy.

31:08.106 --> 31:11.570
So the second facet of joy

31:12.226 --> 31:18.895
is the joy of faith, and it is faith in all that God is for us in Jesus.

31:19.817 --> 31:21.699
This is not joy and given faith away.

31:21.719 --> 31:24.944
This is the joy that's straight up vertical.

31:25.585 --> 31:26.646
You're everything to me.

31:27.647 --> 31:29.310
You have satisfied my heart.

31:30.411 --> 31:31.433
You meet my needs.

31:33.636 --> 31:35.759
The steadfast love of the Lord is better than life.

31:39.083 --> 31:41.106
Third, the third facet.

31:41.954 --> 31:48.000
of joy in these verses is verse 18, it's perhaps the most offensive.

31:51.203 --> 31:59.391
Likewise, you also should be glad and rejoice with me.

32:00.892 --> 32:10.642
So Paul has just said that his joy is the joy of being poured out, that is dying for the sake of their faith,

32:12.354 --> 32:22.905
And now he says, and as I die for your faith, you should be glad with me.

32:26.169 --> 32:36.180
And I can imagine the poor Philippians saying, Paul, this is asking too much.

32:38.382 --> 32:41.746
Can't we have a season of sorrow

32:45.442 --> 32:47.385
Can we grieve when you die?

32:47.425 --> 32:51.270
We love you.

32:54.233 --> 32:55.014
We love you.

32:55.095 --> 32:58.579
What are you asking of us?

33:03.906 --> 33:11.856
To which I think Paul would say, you may indeed grieve when I die.

33:11.876 --> 33:13.138
Let the tears flow.

33:14.754 --> 33:21.443
But don't you dare stop rejoicing with me."

33:21.563 --> 33:35.261
That's why at this school, we love 2 Corinthians 6, 10, sorrowful, yet always rejoicing, simultaneous.

33:39.587 --> 33:41.650
Tell us, can you live in this world?

33:46.530 --> 33:51.496
So there they are, the three facets of joy in these two verses.

33:51.997 --> 34:04.832
Number one, the joy of pouring out your life unto death if necessary for the joy of others as they come to faith or grow in faith.

34:06.214 --> 34:14.203
Second, the joy of faith itself and all that vertically God is for you now and forever.

34:15.385 --> 34:16.306
And third,

34:16.866 --> 34:23.814
rejoicing with those who joyfully die for the sake of other people's faith.

34:25.776 --> 34:26.097
Wow.

34:27.478 --> 34:35.207
You can see why those verses carry a counter-cultural, counter-intuitive wallop.

34:35.868 --> 34:44.818
And I'm arguing now, as I close, that joy, that three faceted joy provides a

34:45.954 --> 35:01.334
an invincible force for the sake of global missions and for the overcoming of the obstacles that get in the way between you and your engagement with more Christianity.

35:04.619 --> 35:05.320
How does that work?

35:05.720 --> 35:06.161
So here we are.

35:07.262 --> 35:13.010
Number one, what becomes, young people, this was the first one,

35:15.266 --> 35:34.112
What becomes of your politically correct cowardice that tries to shut down other people so you feel safe if you are experiencing the joy of pouring out your life for the sake of those very people?

35:37.977 --> 35:41.362
It can't survive in the same heart.

35:42.338 --> 35:46.703
Politically correct cowardice that shuts down others so you feel safe.

35:46.943 --> 35:51.288
Can't survive in the heart that is rejoicing, but I get to die for you.

35:51.308 --> 35:55.293
You can't.

35:56.254 --> 36:06.045
And therefore this joy liberates you from that cowardice, cuts the nerve of that kind of politically correct cowardice.

36:07.346 --> 36:08.848
You don't need to feel safe.

36:09.068 --> 36:10.770
You dare not feel safe.

36:11.906 --> 36:14.990
No missions happens where you have to feel safe.

36:21.199 --> 36:30.431
If I am to be poured out as a drink offering upon the sacrificial offering of your faith, I am glad.

36:30.491 --> 36:33.936
That's not the voice of cowardice.

36:35.718 --> 36:41.266
That's the voice of Christ-treasuring courage and love

36:41.922 --> 36:46.008
and I pray it's your voice.

36:46.028 --> 37:00.469
Second, what becomes the choking cords of consumption in midlife if you drink deeply from the inexhaustible spring of the joy of faith?

37:02.172 --> 37:06.258
So this is the second facet applied to consumption.

37:13.186 --> 37:33.145
If with the psalmist, you go to God and say, I come to you, God, my exceeding joy, and you drink of the river of delights at his right hand, you cut the cords of life-choking consumption.

37:34.426 --> 37:34.806
You do.

37:36.588 --> 37:42.994
If you're drinking at the river of his delights day by day, if you're being satisfied

37:43.106 --> 37:54.020
with all that God is for you in Jesus day by day, you will cut the nerve of unquenchable consumption.

37:54.321 --> 37:54.961
You'll be free.

37:55.963 --> 37:56.543
You'll be free.

37:58.546 --> 38:07.177
The joy of faith is a mighty and powerful liberator.

38:07.197 --> 38:10.802
Number three, what about us old people?

38:12.866 --> 38:14.408
the creep of comfort.

38:18.914 --> 38:26.664
So the third facet here, which I'm aligning with my danger, verse 18.

38:27.746 --> 38:42.866
Likewise, you who you also should be glad, you 80 something, 70 something, 60 something, you should be glad and rejoice with me as I import out on

38:44.002 --> 38:45.304
the faith of the nations.

38:49.189 --> 38:51.953
What would be an application of that?

38:54.556 --> 38:55.217
I'll give you one.

38:56.239 --> 38:56.939
Grandparents.

39:03.088 --> 39:13.682
It implies that a grandparent will never, never, never say to his 20-something, 30-something, 40-something,

39:13.986 --> 39:20.352
Mission-minded children, don't you dare take my babies, my grandbabies, to that place.

39:23.856 --> 39:25.117
You will never say that.

39:32.244 --> 39:40.312
Your child comes to you, you're 30-something child, and says we're feeling a real deep sense.

39:40.372 --> 39:42.674
We should go to fill in the blank.

39:46.306 --> 39:57.905
And we are ready to be poured out our whole family on the sacrificial offering of their face because nobody's telling them anything about the gospel.

39:57.925 --> 39:58.386
Nobody.

40:01.010 --> 40:01.651
And we're ready.

40:05.457 --> 40:09.564
And you would say to them, how could you do that?

40:09.584 --> 40:10.706
How could you do that to me?

40:17.378 --> 40:32.436
Some of us would give both arms to hear a kid say that.

40:32.456 --> 40:33.977
God has a better dream for your life.

40:36.581 --> 40:39.063
Be glad and rejoice with your kids.

40:40.365 --> 40:44.690
Pay their way and go with them.

40:47.426 --> 40:48.888
short term, short term.

40:48.908 --> 40:49.989
That's all you got is short term.

40:59.941 --> 41:13.478
So, dear, dear friends, at the God for Life Conference, let's be done with every obstacle between us and Christ's all nations charge.

41:13.758 --> 41:16.101
Let's be done.

41:16.121 --> 41:16.882
And let us

41:18.050 --> 41:21.095
Be done with politically correct cowardice.

41:21.295 --> 41:23.799
Let's be done with unquenchable consumption.

41:23.839 --> 41:26.823
Let's be done with the creep of comfort.

41:26.903 --> 41:36.437
And let's embrace God's word and the liberating power of joy in giving our lives away for the world.

41:37.739 --> 41:43.067
Even if I'm to be poured out as a drink offering upon the sacrificial offering of your faith, I am glad.

41:45.290 --> 41:46.712
And I rejoice with you all.

41:46.953 --> 41:47.794
Likewise,

41:48.322 --> 41:52.808
You should be glad and rejoice with me.

41:54.691 --> 41:56.994
Father, we're going to sing now.

41:57.034 --> 41:58.175
We need to sing.

41:58.195 --> 42:01.400
And so would you come.

42:01.420 --> 42:17.682
I prayed at the beginning, Father, that those in whom you are already working would feel some sense of confirmation

42:18.018 --> 42:18.919
or guidance.

42:20.501 --> 42:22.903
And I pray that now as we sing, that would be sealed.

42:22.923 --> 42:30.572
I know some really, really big decisions in my life have been made in corporate worship in singing.

42:33.615 --> 42:35.497
Lord, all of us should be world Christians.

42:35.798 --> 42:37.560
Show us how we can be better at that.

42:38.481 --> 42:40.643
Conquer every obstacle in our lives.

42:40.823 --> 42:41.244
I pray.

42:41.704 --> 42:44.027
Bring glory to your name among the nations.

42:44.147 --> 42:47.090
Make us more loving towards the unreached peoples.

42:48.930 --> 42:52.178
I ask this in Jesus name, amen.

